BAUCHI – An All Progressives Congress gubernatorial Aspirant, Muhammad Sani Al-Ameen has called on President Muhammadu Buhari to reappoint Professor Suleiman Elias Bogoro as the Executive Secretary TETFUND, considering all the giant strides recorded in the educational sector under his administration. Muhammad in a press statement signed by him, which made available to newsmen in Bauchi, maintained that the successes and achievements recorded at the TETFUND under Professor Bogoro are unprecedented which are rare and exceptional, adding that personalities like him are needed in the government to drive forward the educational infrastructure, especially at the tertiary level. “It is unarguable that TETFUND has been revived, reactivated and made functional under Professor Bogoro who has brought a new lease of life to tertiary institutions across the length and breadth of Nigeria. His ingenuity and high records of academia have injected and brought new ideas and innovations that are of international standards that have to increase the nation’s tertiary institutions to compete with their counterparts around the world” “He has also established the titan of renowned academics under the leadership of Professor Gadzama and this is the reason behind the world-class infrastructural development in the nation tertiary institutions apart from producing a number of academics reforms to meet with the current world Challenges” “These interventions created in the areas of educational research has given an opportunity to all and sundry to spring up to the peak of academics without regards to the status and background of the researchers. He has renewed and simplified methods of research development, thereby making it an easy ride and more accessible with an emphasis on merits and performance” “Professor Bogoro through TETFUND has sponsored many results-oriented and highly practical research by investing in the training and retraining of Academic Staff in Universities and other tertiary institutions of higher learning in Nigeria. Both local and foreign training got the necessary attention under his watch because of their importance in reviving dwindling Education Sector” ” Nigerian Universities and other tertiary institutions can not afford to lose Professor Bogoro at this very critical situation as previous leaderships have not given the Universities and other tertiary institutions the required training and retraining to meet up with the demand of the 21st century. The celebrations that followed his reinstatement spoke in high volume his capacity and magnitude to oversee the activities of TETFUND without prejudice” “The Federal Government should instead rally round the successes and achievements of Professor Bogoro especially now that his services are needed most to drive the tertiary institutions to compete with their contemporaries at the international level in terms of Research and Development” The statement read in parts.